",["$r","p",null,{"children":"Depending on your background, you can think about splitting up a design into components in different ways:"}],"
",["$r","ul",null,{"children":["
",["$r","li",null,{"children":[["$r","strong",null,{"children":"Programming"}],"—use the same techniques for deciding if you should create a new function or object. One such technique is the ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single_responsibility_principle","target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer","children":"single responsibility principle"}],", that is, a component should ideally only do one thing. If it ends up growing, it should be decomposed into smaller subcomponents."]}],"
